cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.IT

This paper discusses the integration of wireless network virtualization and information-centric networking (ICN) with device-to-device (D2D) communications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses resource allocation optimization, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of content caching in mobile devices is related to cs.MM (Multimedia), and the incorporation of content caching strategies involves cs.IT (Information Theory).
